523  if(!aIndArrowBML){

526  if(actintLowResFlag)

528  else
529  aIndArrowBML -> load("resource/actint/800x600/ind_data/arrow.bml");
530  }
531  if(!aIndDataBML){

636  p -> generate_floor();

638  }

640  ErrH.Abort("Done...");
641 #endif
642 #endif
643 #ifdef _GENERATE_iMATRIX_SHAPES_
644  aci_CellSize = aCellSize;

647  invMatrix* p = (invMatrix*)aScrDisp -> i_matrixList -> last;
648  while(p){
649  p -> generate_shape();

652  }
653  aCellSize = aci_CellSize;
654  build_cell_frame();
655 #ifdef _GENERATE_EXIT_
656  ErrH.Abort("Done...");
657 #endif
658 #endif

696 void aLoadFonts(void)
697 {
698  int i;
699  XBuffer XBuf;
700  XStream fh;
701 
702 #ifdef _ACI_BML_FONTS_
703  if(!aScrFonts)
704  aScrFonts = new aciFont*[AS_NUM_FONTS];
705 #else
706  int sz;
707  char* buf;
708  if(!aScrFonts)
709  aScrFonts = new iScreenFont*[AS_NUM_FONTS];
710 #endif
711 
712  for(i = 0; i < AS_NUM_FONTS; i ++){
713  XBuf.init();
714  XBuf < "resource/actint/fonts/sfont";
715  if(i < 10)
716  XBuf < "0";
717 
718 #ifdef _ACI_BML_FONTS_
719  XBuf <= i < ".bml";
720  aScrFonts[i] = new aciFont;
721  aScrFonts[i] -> load(XBuf.GetBuf());
722  aScrFonts[i] -> calc_offs();
723 #else
724  XBuf <= i < ".fnt";
725  fh.open(XBuf,XS_IN);
726  sz = fh.size();
727 
728  buf = new char[sz];
729  fh.read(buf,sz);
730  fh.close();
731 
732  aScrFonts[i] = new iScreenFont(buf,sz);
733 #endif
734 
735  }
736 }

795 int aStrLen(unsigned char* str,int font,int space)

799  len += aScrFonts[font] -> SizeX - (aScrFonts[font] -> LeftOffs[str[s]] + aScrFonts[font] -> RightOffs[str[s]]) + space;
800  return len;

825 #ifdef _ACI_BML_FONTS_
826 #define ACI_COLOR_MASK 0xFF
827 void aPutStr32(int x,int y,int font,int color,int color_size,void* str,int bsx,void* buf,int space)
828 {
829  int s,xs,ys,offs = 0,sz = strlen((char*)str),X = 0,col,col_sz,col1,col2,col_sz1,col_sz2;
830  int buf_offs = 0;
831 
832  unsigned char* str_buf;
833 
834  if(aScrFonts32[font] == NULL)
835  ErrH.Abort("MISSING FONT...");
836 
837  col1 = color & 0xFF;
838  col2 = (color >> 16) & 0xFF;
839 
840  col_sz1 = color_size & 0xFF;
841  col_sz2 = (color_size >> 16) & 0xFF;
842 
843  unsigned char* p = aScrFonts32[font] -> data;
844  xs = aScrFonts32[font] -> SizeX;
845  ys = aScrFonts32[font] -> SizeY;
846 
847  str_buf = (unsigned char*)str;
848 
849  X = x;
850 
851  for(s = 0; s < sz; s ++){
852  buf_offs = 0;
853  X -= aScrFonts32[font] -> LeftOffs[str_buf[s]];
854 
855  offs = xs * ys * str_buf[s];
856  if(col2){
857  if((str_buf[s] >= 48 && str_buf[s] <= 57) || str_buf[s] == 36){
858  col = col2;
859  col_sz = col_sz2;
860  }
861  else {
862  col = col1;
863  col_sz = col_sz1;
864  }
865  }
866  else {
867  col = col1;
868  col_sz = col_sz1;
869  }
870  aciPutBufSpr(X,y,xs,ys,bsx,p + offs,buf,col,col_sz);
871  X += xs + space - aScrFonts32[font] -> RightOffs[str_buf[s]];
872  }
873 }

875 void aPutStr(int x,int y,int font,int color,unsigned char* str,int bsx,unsigned char* buf,int space)
876 {
877  int i,j,s,xs,ys,offs = 0,sz = strlen((char*)str),X = 0,col1,col2,col3,col4;
878  int buf_index = 0,buf_offs = 0;
879 
880  col1 = color & ACI_COLOR_MASK;
881  col2 = (color >> 8) & ACI_COLOR_MASK;
882 
883  col3 = (color >> 16) & ACI_COLOR_MASK;
884  col4 = (color >> 24) & ACI_COLOR_MASK;
885 
886  if(aScrFonts[font] == NULL)
887  ErrH.Abort("MISSING FONT...");
888 
889  unsigned char* p = aScrFonts[font] -> data;
890  xs = aScrFonts[font] -> SizeX;
891  ys = aScrFonts[font] -> SizeY;
892 
893  buf_index = x + y * bsx;
894 
895  if(col2){
896  for(s = 0; s < sz; s ++){
897  buf_offs = 0;
898  offs = ys * str[s];
899 
900  X -= aScrFonts[font] -> LeftOffs[str[s]];
901 
902  offs = xs * ys * str[s];
903  if((col3 || col4) && ((str[s] >= 48 && str[s] <= 57) || str[s] == 36)){
904  for(i = 0; i < ys; i ++){
905  for(j = 0; j < xs; j ++){
906  switch(p[offs + j]){
907  case 1:
908  buf[X + j + buf_index + buf_offs] = col3;
909  break;
910  case 2:
911  buf[X + j + buf_index + buf_offs] = col4;
912  break;
913  }
914  }
915  offs += xs;
916  buf_offs += bsx;
917  }
918  }
919  else {
920  for(i = 0; i < ys; i ++){
921  for(j = 0; j < xs; j ++){
922  switch(p[offs + j]){
923  case 1:
924  buf[X + j + buf_index + buf_offs] = col1;
925  break;
926  case 2:
927  buf[X + j + buf_index + buf_offs] = col2;
928  break;
929  }
930  }
931  offs += xs;
932  buf_offs += bsx;
933  }
934  }
935  X += xs + space - aScrFonts[font] -> RightOffs[str[s]];
936  }
937  }
938  else {
939  for(s = 0; s < sz; s ++){
940  buf_offs = 0;
941  offs = ys * str[s];
942 
943  X -= aScrFonts[font] -> LeftOffs[str[s]];
944 
945  offs = xs * ys * str[s];
946  if(col3 && ((str[s] >= 48 && str[s] <= 57) || str[s] == 36)){
947  for(i = 0; i < ys; i ++){
948  for(j = 0; j < xs; j ++){
949  switch(p[offs + j]){
950  case 1:
951  buf[X + j + buf_index + buf_offs] = col3;
952  break;
953  }
954  }
955  offs += xs;
956  buf_offs += bsx;
957  }
958  }
959  else {
960  for(i = 0; i < ys; i ++){
961  for(j = 0; j < xs; j ++){
962  switch(p[offs + j]){
963  case 1:
964  buf[X + j + buf_index + buf_offs] = col1;
965  break;
966  }
967  }
968  offs += xs;
969  buf_offs += bsx;
970  }
971  }
972  X += xs + space - aScrFonts[font] -> RightOffs[str[s]];
973  }
974  }
975 }

977 void aOutStr(int x,int y,int font,int color,unsigned char* str,int space)
978 {
979  int i,j,s,xs,ys,offs = 0,sz = strlen((char*)str),X = 0,Y = 0,col1,col2;
980 
981  unsigned char* palBuf = palbuf;
982 
983  col1 = color & ACI_COLOR_MASK;
984  col2 = (color >> 8) & ACI_COLOR_MASK;
985 
986  if(aScrFonts[font] == NULL)
987  ErrH.Abort("MISSING FONT...");
988 
989  unsigned char* p = aScrFonts[font] -> data;
990  xs = aScrFonts[font] -> SizeX;
991  ys = aScrFonts[font] -> SizeY;
992 
993  X = x;
994 
995  if(col2){
996  for(s = 0; s < sz; s ++){
997  offs = ys * str[s];
998 
999  X -= aScrFonts[font] -> LeftOffs[str[s]];
1000 
1001  offs = xs * ys * str[s];
1002  for(i = 0; i < ys; i ++){
1003  Y = y + i;
1004  for(j = 0; j < xs; j ++){
1005  switch(p[offs + j]){
1006  case 1:
1007  XGR_SetPixel(X + j,Y,col1);
1008  break;
1009  case 2:
1010  XGR_SetPixel(X + j,Y,col2);
1011  break;
1012  }
1013  }
1014  offs += xs;
1015  }
1016  X += xs + space - aScrFonts[font] -> RightOffs[str[s]];
1017  }
1018  }
1019  else {
1020  for(s = 0; s < sz; s ++){
1021  offs = ys * str[s];
1022 
1023  X -= aScrFonts[font] -> LeftOffs[str[s]];
1024 
1025  offs = xs * ys * str[s];
1026  for(i = 0; i < ys; i ++){
1027  Y = y + i;
1028  for(j = 0; j < xs; j ++){
1029  switch(p[offs + j]){
1030  case 1:
1031  XGR_SetPixel(X + j,Y,col1);
1032  break;
1033  }
1034  }
1035  offs += xs;
1036  }
1037  X += xs + space - aScrFonts[font] -> RightOffs[str[s]];
1038  }
1039  }
1040 }

1093 void aPutStr(int x,int y,int font,int color,unsigned char* str,int bsx,int bsy,unsigned char* buf,int space)
1094 {

1263 static int aciMapVngColors[11] = { 254, 143, 156, 175, 200, 200, 239, 230, 224, 254, 156 };
1264 
1265 void show_map(int x,int y,int sx,int sy)
1266 {
1267  int i,index,m_index,cx,cy,y0,x_index = 0,_x = 0,_y = 0,vy,sx2,sy2;
1268  int scr_x,scr_y,dx,scr_x0;
1269 
1270  unsigned char* ptr;
1271  bmlObject* p = aScrDisp -> mapObj;
1272 
1273  cx = (ViewX * p -> SizeX) >> MAP_POWER_X;
1274  cy = (ViewY * p -> SizeY) >> MAP_POWER_Y;
1275 
1276  sx2 = sx / 2;
1277  sy2 = sy / 2;
1278 
1279  vy = sy * ((1 << MAP_POWER_Y) / p -> SizeY) / 2;
1280 
1281  y0 = cy - sy2;
1282  if(y0 < 0) y0 += p -> SizeY;
1283  if(y0 >= p -> SizeY) y0 -= p -> SizeY;
1284 
1285  ptr = new unsigned char[sx * sy];
1286  memset(ptr,0,sx * sy);
1287 
1288  if(cx < sx2){
1289  dx = sx2 - cx;
1290 
1291  _y = y0;
1292  index = 0;
1293  m_index = y0 * p -> SizeX + p -> SizeX - dx;
1294  for(i = 0; i < sy; i ++){
1295  memcpy(ptr + index,p -> frames + m_index,dx);
1296 
1297  index += sx;
1298  m_index += p -> SizeX;
1299 
1300  _y ++;
1301  if(_y >= p -> SizeY){
1302  m_index = p -> SizeX - dx;
1303  _y = 0;
1304  }
1305  }
1306 
1307  _y = y0;
1308  index = dx;
1309  m_index = y0 * p -> SizeX;
1310  for(i = 0; i < sy; i ++){
1311  memcpy(ptr + index,p -> frames + m_index,sx - dx);
1312 
1313  index += sx;
1314  m_index += p -> SizeX;
1315 
1316  _y ++;
1317  if(_y >= p -> SizeY){
1318  m_index = 0;
1319  _y = 0;
1320  }
1321  }
1322  }
1323  else {
1324  if(p -> SizeX - cx < sx2){
1325  dx = sx2 - (p -> SizeX - cx);
1326 
1327  _y = y0;
1328  index = 0;
1329  m_index = y0 * p -> SizeX + p -> SizeX - (sx - dx);
1330  for(i = 0; i < sy; i ++){
1331  memcpy(ptr + index,p -> frames + m_index,sx - dx);
1332 
1333  index += sx;
1334  m_index += p -> SizeX;
1335 
1336  _y ++;
1337  if(_y >= p -> SizeY){
1338  m_index = p -> SizeX - (sx - dx);
1339  _y = 0;
1340  }
1341  }
1342 
1343  _y = y0;
1344  index = sx - dx;

1356  }
1357  }

1583 const double _PI128 = 3.14/128.0;
1584 void a_calc_tables(void)
1585 {
1586  int i;
1587  double phi;
1588  if(!aSinTable && !aCosTable){
1589  aSinTable = new int[256];
1590  aCosTable = new int[256];
1591 
1592  for(i = 0; i < 256; i ++){
1593  phi = ((double)i) * _PI128;
1594  aSinTable[i] = (int)(sin(phi) * 256.0);
1595  aCosTable[i] = (int)(cos(phi) * 256.0);
1596  }
1597  }
1598 }

1605 void a_buf_line(int x1,int y1,int x2,int y2,int col,int sx,int sy,unsigned char* buf)
1606 {
1607  int dx,dy,xinc,yinc,err,cnt,index,i_xinc,i_yinc;
1608 
1609  dx = x2 - x1;
1610  dy = y2 - y1;
1611 
1612  xinc = (dx > 0) ? 1 : (dx < 0) ? (-1) : 0;
1613  yinc = (dy > 0) ? 1 : (dy < 0) ? (-1) : 0;
1614 
1615  i_xinc = xinc;
1616  i_yinc = (dy > 0) ? sx : (dy < 0) ? (-sx) : 0;
1617 
1618  dx = abs(dx);
1619  dy = abs(dy);
1620  index = x1 + y1 * sx;
1621  if(dx > dy){
1622  err = dx/2;
1623  cnt = dx + 1;
1624  while(cnt--){
1625  buf[index] = col;
1626  x1 += xinc;
1627  index += i_xinc;
1628 
1629  err += dy;
1630  if(err >= dx){
1631  if(cnt)
1632  buf[index] = col;
1633  err -= dx;
1634  y1 += yinc;
1635  index += i_yinc;
1636  }
1637  }
1638  }
1639  else {
1640  err = dy / 2;
1641  cnt = dy + 1;
1642  while(cnt--){
1643  buf[index] = col;
1644  y1 += yinc;
1645  index += i_yinc;
1646  err += dx;
1647  if(err >= dy){
1648  if(cnt)
1649  buf[index] = col;
1650  err -= dy;
1651  x1 += xinc;
1652  index += i_xinc;
1653  }
1654  }
1655  }
1656 }
1657

1669  i_yinc = (dy > 0) ? sx : (dy < 0) ? (-sx) : 0;

1707 void fill_buf(int fx,int fy,int src_col,int dest_col,int sx,int sy,unsigned char* buf)
1708 {
1709  int x,y,flag = 1,index;
1710 
1711  buf[fx + fy * sx] = dest_col;
1712 
1713  while(flag){
1714  index = 0;
1715  flag = 0;
1716  for(y = 0; y < sy; y ++){
1717  for(x = 0; x < sx; x ++){
1718  if(buf[index] == src_col){
1719  if(x && buf[index - 1] == dest_col){
1720  flag = 1;
1721  buf[index] = dest_col;
1722  }
1723  if(x < sx - 1 && buf[index + 1] == dest_col){
1724  flag = 1;
1725  buf[index] = dest_col;
1726  }
1727  if(y && buf[index - sx] == dest_col){
1728  flag = 1;
1729  buf[index] = dest_col;
1730  }
1731  if(y < sy - 1 && buf[index + sx] == dest_col){
1732  flag = 1;
1733  buf[index] = dest_col;
1734  }
1735  }
1736  index ++;
1737  }
1738  }
1739  }
1740 }

1880 int aciReInitItem(actintItemData* p)

1928 void aciAutoMoveItems(void)
1929 {
1930  int i,x,y,sz;
1931  invItem* p,*p1;
1932  if(!aScrDisp -> curMatrix || !aScrDisp -> secondMatrix)
1933  return;
1934 
1935  p = (invItem*)aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> items -> last;
1936  sz = aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> items -> Size;
1937  for(i = 0; i < sz; i ++){
1938  p1 = (invItem*)p -> prev;
1939  x = p -> MatrixX;
1940  y = p -> MatrixY;
1941  aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> remove_item(p);
1942  if(!aScrDisp -> secondMatrix -> auto_put_item(p)){
1943  aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> put_item(x,y,p);
1944  }
1945  else {
1946  ((uvsActInt*)p -> uvsDataPtr) -> pos_x = p -> MatrixX;
1947  ((uvsActInt*)p -> uvsDataPtr) -> pos_y = p -> MatrixY;
1948  }
1949  p = p1;
1950  }
1951  SOUND_DROP();
1952  aScrDisp -> flags &= ~AS_FULL_REDRAW;
1953 }

2541 void aciNextShopItem(void)
2542 {
2543  invItem* p,*fp;
2544  invMatrix* m,*fm;
2545  if(!iShopItem){
2546  aciInitEvLineID();
2547  aciChangeList();
2548  return;
2549  }
2550 
2551  aciShopMenuDown();
2552 
2553  switch(iEvLineID){
2554  case MECHOS_MODE:
2555  case MECHOS_LIST_MODE:
2556  fm = (invMatrix*)iShopItem;
2557  m = (invMatrix*)fm -> next;
2558  if(m != fm){
2559  while(!m -> uvsDataPtr){
2560  m = (invMatrix*)m -> next;
2561  if(m == fm) break;
2562  }
2563  if(!m -> uvsDataPtr){
2564  iShopItem = NULL;
2565  }
2566  else {
2567  iShopItem = (iListElement*)m;
2568  aciCurMechosID = m -> type;
2569  }
2570  }
2571  break;
2572  case ITEMS_MODE:
2573  case ITEMS_LIST_MODE:
2574  case CHANGE_2_ITEMS_MODE:
2575  fp = (invItem*)iShopItem;
2576  p = (invItem*)fp -> next;
2577  if(p != fp){
2578  while(!p -> uvsDataPtr || p -> classID != AS_ITEM_CLASS){
2579  p = (invItem*)p -> next;
2580  if(p == fp) break;
2581  }
2582  if(!p -> uvsDataPtr || p -> classID != AS_ITEM_CLASS)
2583  iShopItem = NULL;
2584  else
2585  iShopItem = (iListElement*)p;
2586  }
2587  break;
2588  case WEAPONS_MODE:
2589  case WEAPONS_LIST_MODE:
2590  case CHANGE_2_WEAPONS_MODE:
2591  fp = (invItem*)iShopItem;
2592  p = (invItem*)fp -> next;
2593  if(p != fp){
2594  while(!p -> uvsDataPtr || p -> classID != AS_WEAPON_CLASS){
2595  p = (invItem*)p -> next;
2596  if(p == fp) break;
2597  }
2598  if(!p -> uvsDataPtr || p -> classID != AS_WEAPON_CLASS)
2599  iShopItem = NULL;
2600  else
2601  iShopItem = (iListElement*)p;
2602  }
2603  break;
2604  }
2605  aciInitAviID();
2606 }

2795  m -> uvsDataPtr = NULL;

2800  p = (invItem*)aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> items -> last;
2801  while(p){
2802  p -> uvsDataPtr = NULL;

2804  }

2806 
2807 #ifdef _ACI_LOGFILE_
2808  aScrDisp -> logFile < "\r\n\r\nShopItems :\r\n";

2836

2853  p -> uvsDataPtr = u;
2854  break;
2855  }
2856  p = (invItem*)p -> prev;
2857  }
2858  u = (uvsActInt*)u -> next;
2859  }

2861  while(p){

2863  ErrH.Abort("aciInitShopItems failed...");
2864  p = (invItem*)p -> prev;

2866  aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> uvsDataPtr = GGamerMechos;
2867  }
2868  aciChangeList();

2993 void aciSellMoveItem(void)
2994 {
2995  int i,id,fl = 0,index,exclude = 1;
2996  invItem* p,*p1;
2997  invMatrix* m,*m1;
2998  uvsActInt* u,*pu;
2999 
3000  iListElement* prev_item = iShopItem;
3001 
3002  int change_mode = 0,prev_mode = iEvLineID;
3003 
3004  if(!(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_INV_MOVE_ITEM)) return;
3005 
3006  p = aScrDisp -> curItem;
3007  p1 = aScrDisp -> get_iitem(p -> ID);
3008  pu = (uvsActInt*)p -> uvsDataPtr;
3009 
3010  if(!uvsCurrentWorldUnable && p -> partData){
3011  index = -1;
3012  m = (invMatrix*)aScrDisp -> i_matrixList -> last;
3013  while(m){
3014  for(i = 0; i < 2; i ++){
3015  if(m -> uvsDataPtr && m -> type == p -> partData -> baseID[i])
3016  index = i;
3017  }
3018  m = (invMatrix*)m -> prev;
3019  }
3020  if(index != -1)
3021  fl = 1;
3022  }
3023  if(!fl){
3024  id = p -> ID;
3025  if(p -> flags & INV_ITEM_NO_PAY) exclude = 0;
3026  if(p -> classID == AS_ITEM_CLASS && prev_mode != ITEMS_MODE && prev_mode != ITEMS_LIST_MODE){
3027  change_mode = CHANGE_2_ITEMS_MODE;
3028  if(iEvLineID != ITEMS_MODE && iEvLineID != ITEMS_LIST_MODE)
3029  iEvLineID = change_mode;
3030  }
3031  if(p -> classID == AS_WEAPON_CLASS && prev_mode != WEAPONS_MODE && prev_mode != WEAPONS_LIST_MODE){
3032  change_mode = CHANGE_2_WEAPONS_MODE;
3033  if(iEvLineID != WEAPONS_MODE && iEvLineID != WEAPONS_LIST_MODE)
3034  iEvLineID = change_mode;
3035  }
3036 
3037  aciSell_Item(p);
3038  aScrDisp -> flags ^= AS_INV_MOVE_ITEM;
3039 
3040  if(!exclude || !aScrDisp -> curLocData -> ExcludeItems[id]){
3041  iShopItem = p1;
3042  }
3043  else {
3044  aciRemoveUvsItem(pu);
3045  iShopItem = prev_item;
3046  switch(prev_mode){
3047  case ITEMS_MODE:
3048  case ITEMS_LIST_MODE:
3049  change_mode = CHANGE_2_ITEMS_MODE;
3050  break;
3051  case WEAPONS_MODE:
3052  case WEAPONS_LIST_MODE:
3053  change_mode = CHANGE_2_WEAPONS_MODE;
3054  break;
3055  case MECHOS_MODE:
3056  case MECHOS_LIST_MODE:
3057  change_mode = CHANGE_2_MECHOS_MODE;
3058  break;
3059  }
3060  iEvLineID = change_mode;
3061  }
3062  }
3063  else {
3064  m = aScrDisp -> get_imatrix(p -> partData -> baseID[index]);
3065  m1 = aScrDisp -> get_imatrix(p -> partData -> targetID[index]);
3066  if(!m || !m1)
3067  ErrH.Abort("Bad constructor mechos ID...");
3068  if(m1 -> uvsDataPtr)
3069  ErrH.Abort("Duplicate constructor mechos...");
3070 
3071  u = (uvsActInt*)m -> uvsDataPtr;
3072 
3073  u -> type = m1 -> type;
3074  m1 -> uvsDataPtr = u;
3075 
3076  m -> uvsDataPtr = NULL;
3077 
3078  iShopItem = (iListElement*)m1;
3079 
3080  u = (uvsActInt*)p -> uvsDataPtr;
3081  u -> delink(GGamer);
3082  delete u;
3083 
3084  p -> uvsDataPtr = NULL;
3085 
3086  if(m1 -> flags & IM_NOT_COMPLETE){
3087  SOUND_UNICUM_1();
3088  }
3089  else {
3090  SOUND_UNICUM_2();
3091  }
3092 
3093  iEvLineID = CHANGE_2_MECHOS_MODE;
3094  aScrDisp -> flags ^= AS_INV_MOVE_ITEM;
3095  }
3096 
3097  aciInitAviID();
3098  restore_mouse_cursor();
3099 
3100  if(aScrDisp -> iscr_iP){
3101  aScrDisp -> iscr_iP -> free_list();
3102  aScrDisp -> iscr_iP -> set_redraw();
3103  }
3104 
3105  if(fl) iEvLineID = CHANGE_2_MECHOS_MODE;
3106 
3107  aciInitShopAvi();
3108 }

3110 int uvs_aciKillItem(int id,int id1)

3132  u -> type = it -> ID;
3133  }
3134  ret = 1;
3135  }

3137  }

3139  if(aScrDisp -> curItem -> ID == id){
3140  if(id1 == -1){
3141  aScrDisp -> free_item(aScrDisp -> curItem);
3142  aScrDisp -> curItem = NULL;
3143  aScrDisp -> flags ^= AS_INV_MOVE_ITEM;
3144  restore_mouse_cursor();
3145  }
3146  else {
3147  it -> clone(aScrDisp -> curItem);
3148  u = (uvsActInt*)aScrDisp -> curItem -> uvsDataPtr;
3149  u -> type = it -> ID;
3150  set_mouse_cursor(aScrDisp -> curItem -> frame,aScrDisp -> curItem -> ScreenSizeX,aScrDisp -> curItem -> ScreenSizeY);
3151  }
3152  ret = 1;
3153  }
3154  }

3157  aciML_D -> key_trap(AML_KEY,AML_KILL_ELEECH_CODE);

3400  case ITEMS_MODE:

3451 void aciChooseShopItem(void)
3452 {
3453  int x,y,id;
3454 
3455  invItem* p;
3456  invMatrix* m;

3467  y = iMouseY;

3470

3472  switch(iEvLineID){

3474  m = aScrDisp -> get_imatrix(mn -> curFunction);
3475  iShopItem = (iListElement*)m;

3489  iShopItem = (iListElement*)p;

3493  break;
3494  }

3496  else {

3498  id = ((invMatrix*)iShopItem) -> type;
3499  if(id != mn -> curFunction){

3522 //TODO need fast malloc and need rewrite!
3523 void aciInitPanel(InfoPanel* p,unsigned char* str)
3524 {
3525  int i = 0,quit_log = 0,sz = strlen((char*)str),str_len,len,col;
3526  unsigned char* dest_str,*ptr,*tmp_ptr;
3527 
3528  dest_str = new unsigned char[sz + 1];
3529  ptr = new unsigned char[sz + 1];
3530  tmp_ptr = ptr;
3531 
3532  str_len = sz;
3533  strcpy((char*)ptr,(char*)str);
3534  col = (aciCurColorScheme[FM_SELECT_BORDER_COL] << 8) | aciCurColorScheme[FM_SELECT_BORDER_COL];
3535 
3536  while(!quit_log){
3537  strcpy((char*)dest_str,(char*)tmp_ptr);
3538 
3539  if(p -> flags & IP_RANGE_FONT)
3540  len = aStrLen32(dest_str,ACI_PHRASE_FONT,p->hSpace);
3541  else
3542  len = aStrLen(dest_str,ACI_PHRASE_FONT,p->hSpace);
3543  if(len < p->SizeX){
3544  if(p -> items -> Size >= p -> MaxStr){
3545  std::cout<<"Dialog phrase too long..."<<std::endl;
3546  quit_log = 1;
3547  } else {
3548  p->add_item((char*)dest_str,-1,col);
3549  sz -= strlen((char*)dest_str);
3550  strcpy((char*)ptr, (char*)str);
3551  if(sz <= 0) {
3552  quit_log = 1;
3553  } else {
3554  tmp_ptr = ptr + (str_len - sz);
3555  }
3556  }
3557  } else {
3558  i = sz;
3559  while(dest_str[i] != ' '){
3560  i --;
3561  if(i <= 0){
3562  quit_log = 1;
3563  break;
3564  }
3565  }
3566  if(!quit_log)
3567  tmp_ptr[i] = 0;
3568  }
3569  }
3570 
3571  delete[] dest_str;
3572  delete[] ptr;
3573 }

3575 void aciStartSpeech(void)
3576 {
3577  aciML_EventSeq* seq;
3578  int i,unlock_id,prepare2_id,prepare_id,speech_id,end_id,end2_id,lock_id,speech_sz,dropLev = 0;
3579 
3580  InfoPanel* p = aScrDisp -> get_info_panel(ACI_ANSWER_PANEL);
3581  if(!p) return;
3582 
3583  aciSpeechMode = dgMood;
3584 
3585 #ifdef _ACI_ESCAVE_DEBUG_
3586  if(aci_dgMoodNext != -1){
3587  aciSpeechMode = aci_dgMoodNext;
3588  aci_dgMoodNext = -1;
3589  }
3590 #endif
3591  unlock_id = AML_UNLOCK0_SEQ + aciSpeechMode;
3592  prepare2_id = AML_PREPARE0_SEQ2 + aciSpeechMode;
3593  prepare_id = AML_PREPARE0_SEQ + aciSpeechMode;
3594  speech_id = AML_SPEECH0_SEQ + aciSpeechMode;
3595  end_id = AML_END0_SEQ + aciSpeechMode;
3596  end2_id = AML_END0_SEQ2 + aciSpeechMode;
3597  lock_id = AML_LOCK0_SEQ + aciSpeechMode;
3598 
3599  speech_sz = p -> items -> Size;
3600 
3601  aciSpeechSeq -> size = 0;
3602 
3603  for(i = 0; i < AML_MAX_DROP_EVENT; i ++)
3604  aciSpeechSeq -> dropLevel[i] = -1;
3605 
3606  if(aciSpeechBegLocked || !aciSpeechStarted){
3607  seq = aciML_D -> getEventSeq(unlock_id);
3608  if(seq){
3609  aciSpeechSeq -> mergeSeq(seq);
3610  aciSpeechSeq -> dropLevel[dropLev] = seq -> dropLevel[0];
3611  dropLev ++;
3612  }
3613  aciSpeechStarted = 1;
3614  }
3615  seq = aciML_D -> getEventSeq(prepare2_id);
3616  if(seq){
3617  aciSpeechSeq -> mergeSeq(seq);
3618  aciSpeechSeq -> dropLevel[dropLev] = seq -> dropLevel[0];
3619  dropLev ++;
3620  }
3621  seq = aciML_D -> getEventSeq(prepare_id);
3622  if(seq){
3623  aciSpeechSeq -> mergeSeq(seq);
3624  aciSpeechSeq -> dropLevel[dropLev] = seq -> dropLevel[0];
3625  dropLev ++;
3626  }
3627  seq = aciML_D -> getEventSeq(speech_id);
3628  if(seq){
3629  for(i = 0; i < speech_sz; i ++)
3630  aciSpeechSeq -> mergeSeq(seq);
3631  }
3632 
3633  seq = aciML_D -> getEventSeq(end_id);
3634  if(seq){
3635  aciSpeechSeq -> mergeSeq(seq);
3636  aciSpeechSeq -> dropLevel[dropLev] = seq -> dropLevel[0];
3637  dropLev ++;
3638  }
3639  seq = aciML_D -> getEventSeq(end2_id);
3640  if(seq){
3641  aciSpeechSeq -> mergeSeq(seq);
3642  aciSpeechSeq -> dropLevel[dropLev] = seq -> dropLevel[0];
3643  dropLev ++;
3644  }
3645  if(aciSpeechEndLocked){
3646  seq = aciML_D -> getEventSeq(lock_id);
3647  if(seq){
3648  aciSpeechSeq -> mergeSeq(seq);
3649  aciSpeechSeq -> dropLevel[dropLev] = seq -> dropLevel[0];
3650  dropLev ++;
3651  }
3652  }
3653 
3654  aciSpeechSeq -> ChannelID = aciML_D -> curDataSet -> SpeechChannel;
3655  aciML_D -> SeqList[0] -> putSeq(aciSpeechSeq);
3656 
3657  aciSpeechBegLocked = aciSpeechEndLocked;
3658 }

3660 void aciNextPhrase(void)

3662  unsigned char* str;
3663  iScreenObject* obj;
3664  InfoPanel* p = aScrDisp -> get_info_panel(ACI_ANSWER_PANEL);

3699  aciInitPanel(p,str);
3700

3702

3704  aciStartSpeech();

3708 int aciCheckCredits(void)
3709 {
3710  invItem* p;
3711  invMatrix* m;
3712  uvsActInt* u;
3713 
3714  int cr = aciGetCurCredits();
3715 
3716  if(iEvLineID == MECHOS_MODE || iEvLineID == MECHOS_LIST_MODE){
3717  m = (invMatrix*)iShopItem;
3718  u = (uvsActInt*)m -> uvsDataPtr;
3719 
3720  if(m -> flags & IM_NOT_COMPLETE) return 0;
3721  }
3722 
3723  if(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_INV_MOVE_ITEM){
3724  if(aScrDisp -> curItem -> partData) return 1;
3725  if(!((uvsActInt*)aScrDisp -> curItem -> uvsDataPtr) -> sell_price) return 0;
3726  return 1;
3727  }
3728 
3729  if(iEvLineID == EMPTY_MODE)
3730  return 0;
3731 
3732  if(iEvLineID == MECHOS_MODE || iEvLineID == MECHOS_LIST_MODE){
3733  if(u -> price > cr + aciGetCurMatrixPrice()) return 0;
3734  }
3735  else {
3736  p = (invItem*)iShopItem;
3737  u = (uvsActInt*)p -> uvsDataPtr;
3738  if(u -> price > cr) return 0;

4392 void aciPackFile(char* fname)
4393 {
4394  int sz, sz1;
4395  char* p, *p1;
4396 
4397  XStream fh(fname,XS_IN);
4398 
4399  sz1 = sz = fh.size();
4400  sz1+=12;
4401  p = new char[sz];
4402  p1 = new char[sz1];
4403  fh.read(p,sz);
4404  fh.close();
4405 
4406  //sz1 = ZIP_compress(p1,sz,p,sz);
4407  /* ZLIB realization (stalkerg)*/
4408  p1[0] = (char)(8 & 0xFF); //8 it is DEFLATE method
4409  p1[1] = (char)((8 >> 8) & 0xFF);
4410  *(unsigned int*)(p1 + 2) = (unsigned int)sz;
4411  sz1-=2+4;
4412  int stat = compress((Bytef*)(p1+2+4),(uLongf*)&(sz1),(Bytef*)p,sz);
4413  sz1+=2+4;
4414  switch(stat){
4415  //case Z_OK: std::cout<<"Compress ok."<<std::endl; break;
4416  case Z_MEM_ERROR: std::cout<<"not enough memory."<<std::endl; break;
4417  case Z_BUF_ERROR: std::cout<<"not enough room in the output buffer."<<std::endl; break;
4418  };
4419 
4420  fh.open(fname,XS_OUT);
4421  fh.write(p1,sz1);
4422  fh.close();
4423 
4424  delete[] p;
4425  delete[] p1;
4426 }

4428 void aciUnPackFile(char* fname)
4429 {
4430  int sz,sz1;
4431  char* p,*p1;
4432 
4433  XStream fh(fname,XS_IN);
4434 
4435  sz = fh.size();
4436  p = new char[sz];
4437  fh.read(p,sz);
4438  fh.close();
4439 
4440  sz1 = *(unsigned int*)(p + 2) + 12;//ZIP_GetExpandedSize(p);
4441  p1 = new char[sz1];
4442 
4443  //ZIP_expand(p1,sz1,p,sz);
4444  /* ZLIB realization (stalkerg)*/
4445  if(*(short*)(p)) { //if label = 0 not compress
4446  std::cout<<"aciUnPackFile DeCompress "<<fname<<" file."<<std::endl;
4447  int stat = uncompress((Bytef*)p1,(uLongf*)&sz1,(Bytef*)(p+2+4),sz-2-4);
4448  switch(stat){
4449  //case Z_OK: std::cout<<"DeCompress ok."<<std::endl; break;
4450  case Z_MEM_ERROR: std::cout<<"DeCompress not enough memory."<<std::endl; break;
4451  case Z_BUF_ERROR: std::cout<<"DeCompress not enough room in the output buffer."<<std::endl; break;
4452  case Z_DATA_ERROR: std::cout<<"DeCompress error data."<<std::endl; break;
4453  };
4454  } else {
4455  memcpy(p1, p + 2 + 4,(unsigned)(sz - 2 - 4));
4456  }
4457  fh.open(fname,XS_OUT);
4458  fh.write(p1,sz1);
4459  fh.close();
4460 
4461  delete[] p;
4462  delete[] p1;
4463 }

4486 void ibsout(int x,int y,void* ptr)
4487 {
4488  int _x,_y,cnt;
4489  int* offs_table = XGR_Obj.yOffsTable;
4490 
4491  unsigned char* vbuf = XGR_VIDEOBUF;
4492  unsigned char* pbuf = (unsigned char*)ptr;
4493 
4494  cnt = *((int*)pbuf);
4495  pbuf += 4;
4496  while(cnt){
4497  _x = *((int*)pbuf);
4498  pbuf += 4;
4499  _y = *((int*)pbuf);
4500  pbuf += 4;
4501 
4502  memcpy(vbuf + offs_table[_y + y] + _x + x,pbuf,cnt);
4503  pbuf += cnt;
4504 
4505  cnt = *((int*)pbuf);
4506  pbuf += 4;
4507  }
4508 }

4640 void mem_rectangle(int x,int y,int sx,int sy,int bsx,int col_in,int col_out,int mode,void* buf)
4641 {
4642  int i,index,_sx,_sy;
4643  unsigned char* p = (unsigned char*)buf;
4644 
4645  index = x + y * bsx;
4646  memset(p + index,col_out,sx);
4647  for(i = 0; i < sy; i ++){
4648  p[index] = p[index + sx - 1] = col_out;
4649  index += bsx;
4650  }
4651  memset(p + index - bsx,col_out,sx);
4652 
4653  if(mode){
4654  _sx = sx - 2;
4655  _sy = sy - 2;
4656 
4657  if(_sx <= 0 || _sy <= 0) return;
4658  index = (x + 1) + (y + 1) * bsx;
4659  for(i = 0; i < _sy; i ++){
4660  memset(p + index,col_in,_sx);
4661  index += bsx;
4662  }
4663  }
4664 }

4840 void aciPromptData::redraw(int scr_x,int scr_y,int scr_sx,int scr_sy)
4841 {

4849  }

4851

4853  for(i = 0; i < NumStr; i ++){
4854  if(StrBuf[i]){
4855  sy += aScrFonts[font] -> SizeY + ACI_PROMPT_DELTA_Y;
4856  }
4857  }
4858  y = scr_y + (scr_sy - sy) / 2;
4859  }
4860  else
4861  y = scr_y + ACI_PROMPT_OFFSET;
4862 
4863  for(i = 0; i < NumStr; i ++){
4864  if(StrBuf[i]){
4865  sx = aStrLen(StrBuf[i],font,ACI_PROMPT_DELTA_X);
4866  x = scr_x + (scr_sx - sx) / 2;

4871  while(x < 0){
4872  sz = strlen((char*)StrBuf[i]) - 1;
4873  StrBuf[i][sz] = 0;
4874  sx = aStrLen(StrBuf[i],font,ACI_PROMPT_DELTA_X);
4875  x = scr_x + (scr_sx - sx) / 2;
4876  PosX[i] = x;

4878  }

4881  }
4882  }

4951 int acsQuant(void)
4952 {
4953  int ret,k,firstQuant = 0;
4954  if(!acsAllocFlag){
4955  acsAllocFlag = 1;
4956  if(NetworkON) aciKeyboardLocked = 1;
4957  acsScrD -> curScrID = acsScreenID;
4958  acsScrD -> QuantCode = 0;
4959  XGR_MouseObj.DisablePrompt();
4960  XGR_MouseShow();
4961  acsScrD -> alloc_mem();
4962 
4963  if(XGR_MAXX == 800 && !(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_ISCREEN))
4964  acsScrD -> curScr -> ChangeCoords((800 - 640)/2,(600 - 480)/2);
4965 
4966  EffectsOff();
4967  firstQuant = 1;
4968  if(acsScrD -> curScrID >= 3){
4969  aciCloseGate();
4970  acsScrD -> Quant(0);
4971  aciOpenGate();
4972  }
4973  KeyBuf -> clear();
4974  }
4975  while(KeyBuf->size){
4976  SDL_Event *e = KeyBuf->get();
4977  if (e->type == SDL_KEYDOWN) {
4978  k = sdlEventToCode(e);
4979  }
4980  if (e->type == SDL_KEYDOWN || e->type == SDL_TEXTINPUT) {
4981  acsScrD->KeyTrap(0, e);
4982  if (e->key.keysym.scancode == SDL_SCANCODE_ESCAPE && !acsScrD -> QuantCode) {
4983  acsScrD -> QuantCode = 1;
4984  }
4985  }
4986 
4987  }
4988  if(aScrDisp -> flags & aMS_MOVED){
4989  acsScrD -> KeyTrap(iMOUSE_MOVE_CODE, nullptr);
4990  aScrDisp -> flags ^= aMS_MOVED;
4991  if(aciMouseFlagL){
4992  acsScrD -> KeyTrap(iMOUSE_LEFT_MOVE, nullptr);
4993  }
4994  if(aciMouseFlagR){
4995  acsScrD -> KeyTrap(iMOUSE_RIGHT_MOVE, nullptr);
4996  }
4997  }
4998  if(aScrDisp -> flags & aMS_LEFT_PRESS){
4999  acsScrD -> KeyTrap(iMOUSE_LEFT_PRESS_CODE, nullptr);
5000  aScrDisp -> flags ^= aMS_LEFT_PRESS;
5001  }
5002  if(aScrDisp -> flags & aMS_RIGHT_PRESS){
5003  acsScrD -> KeyTrap(iMOUSE_RIGHT_PRESS_CODE, nullptr);
5004  aScrDisp -> flags ^= aMS_RIGHT_PRESS;
5005  }
5006  if(NetworkON){
5007  acsScrD -> flags |= ACS_FORCED_REDRAW;
5008  ret = acsScrD -> Quant(actIntLog);
5009  }
5010  else
5011  ret = acsScrD -> Quant();
5012 
5013  if(firstQuant){
5014  acsPrepareSlotNameInput(acsCurrentSlotID,acsCurrentSlotNum);
5015  acsScrD -> PrepareInput(acsCurrentSlotID);
5016  }
5017  if(ret){
5018  acsAllocFlag = 0;
5019  if(XGR_MAXX == 800 && !(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_ISCREEN))
5020  acsScrD -> curScr -> ChangeCoords(-(800 - 640)/2,-(600 - 480)/2);
5021  acsScrD -> free_mem();
5022  if(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_FULLSCR && !(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_ISCREEN)){
5023  XGR_MouseHide();
5024  }
5025  else
5026  aScrDisp -> flags &= ~AS_FULL_REDRAW;
5027 
5028  iScrDisp -> flags &= ~MS_LEFT_PRESS;
5029  iScrDisp -> flags &= ~MS_RIGHT_PRESS;
5030  iScrDisp -> flags &= ~MS_MOVED;
5031  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_TUTORIAL_MODE);
5032  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_SOUND_MODE);
5033  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_SOUND_VOLUME);
5034 
5035  if(NetworkON) aciKeyboardLocked = 0;
5036 
5037  acsScreenID = 1;
5038  iSaveData();
5039  KeyBuf -> clear();
5040  return 1;
5041  }

5045 void acsHandleExtEvent(int code,int data0,int data1,int data2)
5046 {
5047  int val,max_val,i_val,i_max_val;
5048  switch(code){
5049  case ACS_GLOBAL_EXIT:
5050  if(!(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_ISCREEN))
5051  GameQuantReturnValue = RTO_LOADING3_ID;
5052  else {
5053  iScrDisp -> flags |= SD_EXIT;
5054  iScrExitCode = 1;
5055  iAbortGameFlag = 1;
5056  }
5057  if(NetworkON) iMultiFlag = 1;
5058  acsScrD -> QuantCode = 1; // resume game pause
5059  if(!GameOverID)
5060  GameOverID = GAME_OVER_ABORT;
5061  break;
5062  case ACS_INIT_TUTORIAL_MODE:
5063  acsSetStrState(ACS_TUTORIAL_MODE,!iGetOptionValue(iTUTORIAL_ON));
5064  break;
5065  case ACS_SET_TUTORIAL_MODE:
5066  iSetOptionValue(iTUTORIAL_ON,!acsGetStrState(ACS_TUTORIAL_MODE));
5067  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_TUTORIAL_MODE);
5068  break;
5069  case ACS_SET_AUTORUN_MODE:
5070  aciAutoRun = acsGetStrState(ACS_AUTORUN_MODE);
5071  iScrOpt[iAUTO_ACCELERATION]->SetValueINT(acsGetStrState(ACS_AUTORUN_MODE));
5072  break;
5073  case ACS_SET_SOUND_MODE:
5074  iSetOptionValue(iSOUND_ON,!acsGetStrState(ACS_SOUND_MODE));
5075  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_SOUND_MODE);
5076  break;
5077  case ACS_SET_MUSIC_MODE:
5078  iSetOptionValue(iMUSIC_ON,!acsGetStrState(ACS_MUSIC_MODE));
5079  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_MUSIC_MODE);
5080  break;
5081  case ACS_INIT_AUTORUN_MODE:
5082 // acsSetStrState(ACS_AUTORUN_MODE,aciAutoRun);
5083  aciAutoRun = iGetOptionValue(iAUTO_ACCELERATION);
5084  acsSetStrState(ACS_AUTORUN_MODE,iGetOptionValue(iAUTO_ACCELERATION));
5085  break;
5086  case ACS_INIT_SOUND_MODE:
5087  acsSetStrState(ACS_SOUND_MODE,!iGetOptionValue(iSOUND_ON));
5088  break;
5089  case ACS_INIT_SOUND_VOLUME:
5090  acsScrD -> SetScroller(ACS_SOUND_VOLUME,iGetOptionValue(iSOUND_VOLUME_CUR),iGetOptionValue(iSOUND_VOLUME_MAX));
5091  break;
5092  case ACS_SET_SOUND_VOLUME:
5093  val = acsScrD -> GetObjectValue(ACS_SOUND_VOLUME);
5094  max_val = acsScrD -> GetObjectValue(ACS_SOUND_VOLUME,1);
5095  i_max_val = iGetOptionValue(iSOUND_VOLUME_MAX);
5096  i_val = (val * i_max_val) / max_val;
5097  iSetOptionValue(iSOUND_VOLUME_CUR,i_val);
5098  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_SOUND_VOLUME);
5099  break;
5100  case ACS_INIT_MUSIC_MODE:
5101  acsSetStrState(ACS_MUSIC_MODE,!iGetOptionValue(iMUSIC_ON));
5102  break;
5103  case ACS_INIT_MUSIC_VOLUME:
5104  acsScrD -> SetScroller(ACS_MUSIC_VOLUME,iGetOptionValue(iMUSIC_VOLUME_CUR),iGetOptionValue(iMUSIC_VOLUME_MAX));
5105  break;
5106  case ACS_SET_MUSIC_VOLUME:
5107  val = acsScrD -> GetObjectValue(ACS_MUSIC_VOLUME);
5108  max_val = acsScrD -> GetObjectValue(ACS_MUSIC_VOLUME,1);
5109  i_max_val = iGetOptionValue(iMUSIC_VOLUME_MAX);
5110  i_val = (val * i_max_val) / max_val;
5111  iSetOptionValue(iMUSIC_VOLUME_CUR,i_val);
5112  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_MUSIC_VOLUME);
5113  break;
5114  case ACS_CHANGE_MUSIC_MODE:
5115  acsChangeStrState(ACS_MUSIC_MODE);
5116  iSetOptionValue(iMUSIC_ON,!acsGetStrState(ACS_MUSIC_MODE));
5117  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_MUSIC_MODE);
5118  break;
5119  case ACS_CHANGE_AUTORUN_MODE:
5120  acsChangeStrState(ACS_AUTORUN_MODE);
5121  aciAutoRun = acsGetStrState(ACS_AUTORUN_MODE);
5122  iScrOpt[iAUTO_ACCELERATION]->SetValueINT(acsGetStrState(ACS_AUTORUN_MODE));
5123  break;
5124  case ACS_CHANGE_SOUND_MODE:
5125  acsChangeStrState(ACS_SOUND_MODE);
5126  iSetOptionValue(iSOUND_ON,!acsGetStrState(ACS_SOUND_MODE));
5127  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_SOUND_MODE);
5128  break;
5129  case ACS_CHANGE_TUTORIAL_MODE:
5130  acsChangeStrState(ACS_TUTORIAL_MODE);
5131  iSetOptionValue(iTUTORIAL_ON,!acsGetStrState(ACS_TUTORIAL_MODE));
5132  iHandleExtEvent(iEXT_UPDATE_TUTORIAL_MODE);
5133  break;
5134  case ACS_INIT_SLOT_NAME:
5135  acsPrepareSlotName(data0,data1);
5136  break;
5137  case ACS_INIT_SLOT_NAME_INPUT:
5138  acsPrepareSlotNameInput(data0,data1);
5139  break;
5140  case ACS_SAVE_GAME:
5141  acsSaveData();
5142  break;
5143  }
5144 }

5184

5305 void acsLoadData(void)
5306 {
5307  int slot = iSlotNumber,len,time_len;
5308  XBuffer XBuf;
5309  XStream fh;
5310 
5311  if(slot != -1){
5312  XBuf < "savegame/save";
5313  if(slot < 10) XBuf < "0";
5314  XBuf <= slot < ".dat";
5315 
5316 #ifdef _ACI_PACK_SAVES_
5317  acsDecompressData(XBuf.address());
5318 #endif
5319  std::cout<<"acsLoadData"<<std::endl;
5320  fh.open(XBuf.address(),XS_IN);
5321  fh > len;
5322  time_len = (len >> 16) & 0xFF;
5323  len &= 0xFF;
5324  fh.seek(len + sizeof(int) + time_len,XS_BEG);
5325  uniVangLoad(fh);
5326 
5327  aciLoadUVSList(fh,&GItem,1);
5328  aciLoadUVSList(fh,&GMechos);
5329  aciLoadUVSList(fh,&GGamer,1);
5330  aciLoadUVSList(fh,&GGamerMechos);
5331  aciLoadUVSList(fh,&GCharItem,1);
5332  aciLoadUVSList(fh,&GTreasureItem,1);
5333 
5334  aScrDisp->load_data(&fh);
5335  //stalkerg Попытемся проверить трюм магазина и трюм мехоса в мире
5336  //Эти трюмы должны совпадать по содержимому, а иначе игра будет умирать
5337  if(aScrDisp->curMatrix) { //Существует ли матрица
5338  listElem *el = NULL;
5339  listElem *el2 = NULL;
5340  uvsActInt *new_item = NULL;
5341  uvsActInt *iter_gamer = (uvsActInt*)GGamer;
5342  invItem* p,*p1;
5343  while (iter_gamer) {
5344  bool item_detect = false;
5345  int i, j, index = 0;
5346  for(i = 0; i < aScrDisp->curMatrix->SizeY; i++){
5347  for(j = 0; j < aScrDisp->curMatrix->SizeX; j++){
5348  invMatrixCell *cell = aScrDisp->curMatrix->matrix[index];
5349  /*std::cout<<"GGamer type:"<<iter_gamer->type
5350  <<" x:"<<iter_gamer->pos_x
5351  <<" y:"<<iter_gamer->pos_y
5352  <<" i:"<<i
5353  <<" j:"<<j
5354  <<" mcell flags:"<<cell->flags
5355  <<" mcell type:"<<cell->type
5356  <<" index:"<<index<<std::endl;*/
5357  if(cell->flags & AS_BUSY_CELL && cell->item) {
5358  /*std::cout<<"item_type:"<<cell->item->ID
5359  <<" MX:"<<cell->item->MatrixX
5360  <<" MY:"<<cell->item->MatrixY<<std::endl;*/
5361  if (cell->item->ID == iter_gamer->type &&
5362  cell->item->MatrixX == iter_gamer->pos_x &&
5363  cell->item->MatrixY == iter_gamer->pos_y
5364  ) {
5365  item_detect = true;
5366  goto end_find;
5367  }
5368  }
5369  index++;
5370  }
5371  }
5372  std::cout<<"Can't find item GGamer type:"<<iter_gamer->type
5373  <<" pos_x:"<<iter_gamer->pos_x
5374  <<" pos_y:"<<iter_gamer->pos_y
5375  <<" and we make it"<<std::endl;
5376  if(aScrDisp->flags & AS_ISCREEN)
5377  p = aScrDisp->get_iitem(iter_gamer->type);
5378  else
5379  p = aScrDisp->get_item(iter_gamer->type);
5380 
5381  p1 = aScrDisp->alloc_item();
5382  p->clone(p1);
5383  aScrDisp->curMatrix->put_item(iter_gamer->pos_x, iter_gamer->pos_y, p1, 1);
5384  end_find:
5385  //Is it duplicate?
5386  if (el != NULL) {
5387  el2 = el;
5388  while (el2) {
5389  uvsActInt *item = dynamic_cast<uvsActInt*> (el2);
5390  if (item->pos_x == iter_gamer->pos_x && item->pos_y == iter_gamer->pos_y && item->type == iter_gamer->type) {
5391  std::cout<<"We find duplicate item GGamer type:"<<iter_gamer->type
5392  <<" pos_x:"<<iter_gamer->pos_x
5393  <<" pos_y:"<<iter_gamer->pos_y
5394  <<std::endl;
5395  goto next;
5396  }
5397  el2 = el2->next;
5398  }
5399  }
5400  new_item = new uvsActInt;
5401  new_item->pos_x = iter_gamer->pos_x;
5402  new_item->pos_y = iter_gamer->pos_y;
5403  new_item->type = iter_gamer->type;
5404  new_item->price = iter_gamer->price;
5405  new_item->sell_price = iter_gamer->sell_price;
5406  new_item->param1 = iter_gamer->param1;
5407  new_item->param2 = iter_gamer->param2;
5408  new_item->link(el);
5409 
5410  next:
5411  iter_gamer = (uvsActInt*)iter_gamer->next;
5412  }
5413 
5414  aciFreeUVSList(GGamer);
5415  GGamer = (uvsActInt*)el;
5416 
5417  }
5418  GeneralSystemLoad(fh);
5419  dgD -> load(fh);
5420  fh.close();
5421 
5422 #ifdef _ACI_PACK_SAVES_
5423  acsCompressData(XBuf.address());
5424 #endif
5425  }
5426 }

5603  }
5604  p = (fncMenuItem*)mn -> inactive_items -> last;
5605  while(p){
5606  p1 = (fncMenuItem*)p -> prev;
5607  if(p -> fnc_code != FMENU_OFF){
5608  mn -> inactive_items -> dconnect((iListElement*)p);
5609  aScrDisp -> free_menu_item(p);
5610  }
5611  p = p1;
5612  }
5613  mn -> prefix = NULL;
5614  mn -> postfix = NULL;
5615 }

5739 #ifdef _DEBUG
5740 void scale_bmp(int sx,int sy,int sx0,int sy0,void* dest,void* src)
5741 {
5742  int x,y;
5743  unsigned char* dest_buf,*src_buf;
5744 
5745  double ix,iy,dx,dy;
5746 
5747  dest_buf = (unsigned char*)dest;
5748  src_buf = (unsigned char*)src;
5749 
5750  dx = (double)sx0/(double)sx;
5751  dy = (double)sy0/(double)sy;
5752  for(y = 0; y < sy; y ++){
5753  for(x = 0; x < sx; x ++){
5754  iy = y * dy;
5755  ix = x * dx;
5756  dest_buf[x + y * sx] = src_buf[round(ix) + (round(iy) * sx0)];
5757  }
5758  }
5759 }

5761 void aciResizeItem(double delta)
5762 {
5763  int x,y;
5764  invItem* p,*p0;
5765  unsigned char* buf;
5766 
5767  double dx,dy;
5768 
5769  p0 = NULL;
5770 
5771  if(!(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_INV_MOVE_ITEM)) return;
5772  p = aScrDisp -> curItem;
5773 
5774  x = p -> ScreenSizeX;
5775  y = p -> ScreenSizeY;
5776 
5777  dy = (double)y * delta;
5778  dx = ((double)x * dy) / (double)y;
5779  x = round(dx);
5780  y = round(dy);
5781 
5782  if(x < 0 || y < 0) return;
5783  buf = new unsigned char[x * y];
5784  scale_bmp(x,y,p -> ScreenSizeX,p -> ScreenSizeY,buf,p -> frame);
5785  delete p -> frame;
5786  p -> frame = (char*)buf;
5787  p -> ScreenSizeX = x;
5788  p -> ScreenSizeY = y;
5789  set_mouse_cursor((char*)buf,x,y);
5790 
5791  if(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_ISCREEN)
5792  p0 = aScrDisp -> get_iitem(p -> ID);
5793  else
5794  p0 = aScrDisp -> get_item(p -> ID);
5795 
5796  if(p0){
5797  p0 -> ScreenSizeX = x;
5798  p0 -> ScreenSizeY = y;
5799  p0 -> frame = (char*)buf;
5800  }
5801 }

6121 //znfo key handler
6122 void aciCHandler(int key)
6123 {
6124  return;
6125  int code = 0,cr;
6126  if(NetworkON || key > 256 || key <= 0) return;
6127 
6128  if(aciTreeData) {
6129  code = aciTreeData -> quant(key);
6130  }
6131  switch(code << NetworkON){
6132  case ACI_ADD_BEEBOS:
6133  cr = aciGetCurCredits();
6134  cr += 50000;
6135  aciUpdateCurCredits(cr);
6136  if(!(aScrDisp -> flags & AS_ISCREEN))
6137  SetWorldBeebos(cr);
6138  aciTreeData -> reset();
6139  SOUND_DROP();
6140  break;
6141  case ACI_ADD_LUCK:
6142  uvsChangeLuck();
6143  aciTreeData -> reset();
6144  SOUND_DROP();
6145  break;
6146  case ACI_ADD_DOMINANCE:
6147  uvsChangeDominance();
6148  aciTreeData -> reset();
6149  SOUND_DROP();
6150  break;

6352 void aciPutBufSpr(int x,int y,int sx,int sy,int bsx,void* src,void* dest,int col,int col_sz)
6353 {
6354  int i,j,dest_index,src_index;
6355  unsigned src_col;
6356  unsigned char* src_buf,*dest_buf;
6357 
6358  dest_index = x + y * bsx;
6359  src_index = 0;
6360 
6361  src_buf = (unsigned char*)src;
6362  dest_buf = (unsigned char*)dest;
6363 
6364  if(!col_sz){
6365  for(i = 0; i < sy; i ++){
6366  for(j = 0; j < sx; j ++){
6367  src_col = src_buf[src_index + j];
6368  if(src_col)
6369  dest_buf[dest_index + j] = col + src_col;
6370  }
6371  dest_index += bsx;
6372  src_index += sx;
6373  }
6374  }
6375  else {
6376  for(i = 0; i < sy; i ++){
6377  for(j = 0; j < sx; j ++){
6378  src_col = src_buf[src_index + j];
6379  if(src_col)
6380  dest_buf[dest_index + j] = col + (src_col >> col_sz);
6381  }
6382  dest_index += bsx;
6383  src_index += sx;
6384  }
6385  }
6386 }

6396 void aOutText32(int x,int y,int color,void* text,int font,int hspace,int vspace)
6397 {
6398  int s,xs,ys,offs = 0,sz = strlen((char*)text),X = 0,Y = 0;
6399  int color_size,chr;
6400 
6401  unsigned char* str_buf;
6402 
6403  if(aScrFonts32[font] == NULL)
6404  ErrH.Abort("MISSING FONT...");
6405 
6406  color_size = (color >> 16) & 0xFF;
6407  color &= 0xFFFF;
6408 
6409  unsigned char* p = aScrFonts32[font] -> data;
6410  xs = aScrFonts32[font] -> SizeX;
6411  ys = aScrFonts32[font] -> SizeY;
6412 
6413  str_buf = (unsigned char*)text;
6414 
6415  X = x;
6416  Y = y;
6417 
6418  for(s = 0; s < sz; s ++){
6419  chr = str_buf[s];
6420  if(chr != '\n'){
6421  if(chr != '\r'){
6422  X -= aScrFonts32[font] -> LeftOffs[chr];
6423  offs = xs * ys * chr;
6424  aciPutSpr32(X,Y,xs,ys,p + offs,color,color_size);
6425  X += xs + hspace - aScrFonts32[font] -> RightOffs[chr];
6426  }
6427  }
6428  else {
6429  X = x;
6430  Y += ys + vspace;
6431  }
6432  }
6433 }

6474 int aTextWidth32(void* text,int font,int hspace)
6475 {

6477  int len = 0,max_len = 0;
6478 
6479  unsigned char* str_buf;
6480 
6481  if(aScrFonts32[font] == NULL)
6482  ErrH.Abort("MISSING FONT...");
6483 
6484  xs = aScrFonts32[font] -> SizeX;
6485  ys = aScrFonts32[font] -> SizeY;
6486 
6487  str_buf = (unsigned char*)text;
6488 
6489  for(s = 0; s < sz; s ++){
6490  chr = str_buf[s];
6491  if(chr != '\n'){
6492  if(chr != '\r'){
6493  len += xs + hspace - aScrFonts32[font] -> RightOffs[chr] - aScrFonts32[font] -> LeftOffs[chr];
6494  }
6495  }
6496  else {
6497  if(len > max_len) max_len = len;
6498  len = 0;
6499  }
6500  }
6501  if(len > max_len) max_len = len;
6502  return max_len;

6589 void acsCompressData(char* p)
6590 {
6591  int len,time_len,flags,sz,data;
6592  unsigned long dest_sz, src_sz;
6593  XStream fh;
6594 
6595  char* header,*src_buf,*dest_buf;
6596 
6597  fh.open(p,XS_IN);
6598  sz = fh.size();
6599  fh > len;
6600 
6601  time_len = (len >> 16) & 0xFF;
6602  flags = (len >> 24) & 0xFF;
6603  len &= 0xFF;
6604 
6605  if(flags & ACI_SAVE_COMPRESSED){
6606  fh.close();
6607  return;
6608  }
6609 
6610  dest_sz = src_sz = sz - time_len - len - sizeof(int);
6611  dest_sz*=2;
6612  header = new char[len + time_len];
6613  src_buf = new char[src_sz];
6614  dest_buf = new char[dest_sz];
6615 
6616  fh.read(header,len + time_len);
6617  fh.read(src_buf,src_sz);
6618  fh.close();
6619 
6620  //std::cout<<"compress src_sz:"<<src_sz<<std::endl;
6621  //dest_sz = ZIP_compress(dest_buf,src_sz,src_buf,src_sz);
6622  /* ZLIB realization (stalkerg)*/
6623  dest_buf[0] = (char)(8 & 0xFF); //8 it is DEFLATE method
6624  dest_buf[1] = (char)((8 >> 8) & 0xFF);
6625  *(unsigned int*)(dest_buf + 2) = (unsigned int)src_sz;
6626  dest_sz-=2+4;
6627  int stat = compress((Bytef*)(dest_buf+2+4),(uLongf*)&(dest_sz),(Bytef*)src_buf,src_sz);
6628  dest_sz+=2+4;
6629  switch(stat){
6630  //case Z_OK: std::cout<<"Compress ok."<<std::endl; break;
6631  case Z_MEM_ERROR: std::cout<<"not enough memory."<<std::endl; break;
6632  case Z_BUF_ERROR: std::cout<<"not enough room in the output buffer."<<std::endl; break;
6633  };
6634  //std::cout<<"compress dest_sz:"<<dest_sz<<std::endl;
6635  flags |= ACI_SAVE_COMPRESSED;
6636  data = len | ((time_len | (flags << 8)) << 16);
6637 
6638  fh.open(p,XS_OUT);
6639  fh < data;
6640 
6641  fh.write(header,len + time_len);
6642  fh.write(dest_buf,dest_sz);
6643  fh.close();
6644 
6645  delete[] header;
6646  delete[] src_buf;
6647  delete[] dest_buf;
6648 }
6649 
6650 void acsDecompressData(char* p)
6651 {
6652  int len,time_len,flags,sz,data;
6653  XStream fh;
6654  unsigned long dest_sz, src_sz;
6655  char* header,*src_buf,*dest_buf;
6656 
6657  fh.open(p,XS_IN);
6658  sz = fh.size();
6659  fh > len;
6660 
6661  time_len = (len >> 16) & 0xFF;
6662  flags = (len >> 24) & 0xFF;
6663  len &= 0xFF;
6664 
6665  if(!(flags & ACI_SAVE_COMPRESSED)){
6666  fh.close();
6667  return;
6668  }
6669 
6670  src_sz = sz - time_len - len - sizeof(int);
6671  header = new char[len + time_len];
6672  src_buf = new char[src_sz];
6673 
6674  fh.read(header,len + time_len);
6675  fh.read(src_buf,src_sz);
6676  fh.close();
6677 
6678  //dest_sz = ZIP_GetExpandedSize(src_buf);
6679  dest_sz = *(unsigned int*)(src_buf + 2) + 12; //+12 for size need for zlib
6680  dest_buf = new char[dest_sz];
6681 
6682  //ZIP_expand(dest_buf,dest_sz,src_buf,src_sz);
6683  /* ZLIB realisation (stalkerg)*/
6684  if(*(short*)(src_buf)) { //if label = 0 not compress
6685  //std::cout<<"acsDecompressData DeCompress "<<p<<" file."<<std::endl;
6686  int stat = uncompress((Bytef*)dest_buf,(uLongf*)&dest_sz,(Bytef*)(src_buf+2+4),src_sz-2-4);
6687  switch(stat){
6688  //case Z_OK: std::cout<<"DeCompress ok."<<std::endl; break;
6689  case Z_MEM_ERROR: std::cout<<"not enough memory."<<std::endl; break;
6690  case Z_BUF_ERROR: std::cout<<"not enough room in the output buffer."<<std::endl; break;
6691  case Z_DATA_ERROR: std::cout<<"error data."<<std::endl; break;
6692  };
6693  } else {
6694  memcpy(dest_buf,src_buf + 2 + 4,(unsigned)(src_sz - 2 - 4));
6695  }
6696 
6697  flags &= ~ACI_SAVE_COMPRESSED;
6698  data = len | ((time_len | (flags << 8)) << 16);
6699 
6700  fh.open(p,XS_OUT);
6701  fh < data;
6702 
6703  fh.write(header,len + time_len);
6704  fh.write(dest_buf,dest_sz);
6705  fh.close();
6706 
6707  delete[] header;
6708  delete[] src_buf;
6709  delete[] dest_buf;
6710 }

6817 void aciInitItmTextQueue(void)
6818 {
6819  int i;
6820  invItem* p;
6821  for(i = 0; i < ACI_ITEM_QUEUE_MAX; i ++){
6822  aciItmTextQueue[i] = NULL;
6823  }
6824  aciItmTextQueueSize = aciItmTextQueueCur = 0;
6825 
6826  p = (invItem*)aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> items -> last;
6827  while(p){
6828  if(aciItmTextQueueSize < ACI_ITEM_QUEUE_MAX && p -> ID == ACI_TABUTASK && (p -> flags & INV_ITEM_NEW)){
6829  aciItmTextQueue[aciItmTextQueueSize] = p;
6830  aciItmTextQueueSize ++;
6831  }
6832  p = (invItem*)p -> prev;
6833  }
6834  p = (invItem*)aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> items -> last;
6835  while(p){
6836  if(aciItmTextQueueSize < ACI_ITEM_QUEUE_MAX && (p -> ID == ACI_ELEEPOD || p -> ID == ACI_BEEBOORAT || p -> ID == ACI_ZEEX) && (p -> flags & INV_ITEM_NEW)){
6837  aciItmTextQueue[aciItmTextQueueSize] = p;
6838  aciItmTextQueueSize ++;
6839  }
6840  p = (invItem*)p -> prev;
6841  }
6842  p = (invItem*)aScrDisp -> curMatrix -> items -> last;
6843  while(p){
6844  p -> flags &= ~INV_ITEM_NEW;
6845  p = (invItem*)p -> prev;
6846  }
6847 }

7019 int aciTextQuant(void)
7020 {
7021  int ret = 0;
7022  ShowImageRTO* p = (ShowImageRTO*)xtGetRuntimeObject(RTO_SHOW_IMAGE_ID);
7023 
7024  if(aciImgText -> flags & ACI_TEXT_INIT){
7025  ret = 0;
7026  if(ShowImageMouseFlag || ShowImageKeyFlag){
7027  if(aciImgText -> flags & ACI_TEXT_END)
7028  ret = 1;
7029  else {
7030  aciImgText -> NextPage();
7031  if(aciImgText -> flags & ACI_TEXT_END){
7032  if(p -> imageData){
7033  XGR_PutSpr(0,0,p -> imageSX,p -> imageSY,p -> imageData,XGR_BLACK_FON);
7034  }
7035  else {
7036  XGR_Fill(0);
7037  }
7038  XGR_Flush(0,0,XGR_MAXX,XGR_MAXY);
7039  }
7040  }
7041 
7042  ShowImageMouseFlag = ShowImageKeyFlag = 0;
7043  }
7044  aciImgText -> Quant();
7045  if(!(aciImgText -> flags & ACI_TEXT_REDRAW)){
7046  if(p -> imageData){
7047  XGR_PutSpr(0,0,p -> imageSX,p -> imageSY,p -> imageData,XGR_BLACK_FON);
7048  }
7049  else {
7050  XGR_Fill(0);
7051  }
7052  aciImgText -> redraw();
7053  XGR_Flush(0,0,XGR_MAXX,XGR_MAXY);
7054  }
7055  }
7056  else {
7057  if(ShowImageMouseFlag || ShowImageKeyFlag)
7058  ret = 1;
7059  }
7060  return ret;
7061 }

7063 void aciPrepareScreenText(char* ptr,int sz,int max_len)
7064 {
7065  int i,offs_start,offs_end,offs;
7066 
7067 // XStream fh("text0.dat",XS_OUT);
7068 // fh.write(ptr,sz);
7069 // fh.close();
7070 
7071  offs_start = offs_end = 0;
7072  while(offs_start < sz - 1){
7073  while(ptr[offs_end] != '\n'){
7074  offs_end ++;
7075  if(offs_end >= sz){
7076  offs_end = sz - 1;
7077  break;
7078  }
7079  }
7080  if(offs_end - offs_start > max_len){
7081  offs = offs_start + max_len;
7082  for(i = 0; i < max_len; i ++){
7083  if(ptr[offs] == ' ' || ptr[offs] == '\t'){
7084  break;
7085  }
7086  offs --;
7087  if(offs <= offs_start){
7088  break;
7089  }
7090  }
7091  ptr[offs] = '\n';
7092  if(offs > offs_start){
7093  offs_start = offs;
7094  offs_end = offs + 1;
7095  }
7096  else {
7097  offs_start = offs_end;
7098  offs_end ++;
7099  }
7100  }
7101  else {
7102  offs_start = offs_end;
7103  offs_end ++;
7104  }
7105  }
7106 
7107 // fh.open("text1.dat",XS_OUT);
7108 // fh.write(ptr,sz);
7109 // fh.close();
7110 }

7127 char* aciLoadPackedFile(XStream& fh,int& out_sz) //Text decompress
7128 {
7129  int sz;
7130  char *p,*ptr;
7131 
7132  sz = fh.size();
7133  p = new char[sz];
7134  fh.read(p,sz);
7135 
7136  out_sz = *(unsigned int*)(p + 2);
7137  long long_out_sz = out_sz;
7138  ptr = new char[out_sz];
7139 
7140  //ZIP_expand(ptr,out_sz,p,sz);
7141  /* ZLIB realisation (stalkerg)*/
7142  if(*(short*)(p)) { //if label = 0 not compress
7143  //std::cout<<"aciLoadPackedFile DeCompress "<<fh.file_name<<" file."<<std::endl;
7144  int stat = uncompress((Bytef*)ptr,(uLongf*)&long_out_sz,(Bytef*)(p+2+4),sz-2-4);
7145  switch(stat){
7146  //case Z_OK: std::cout<<"DeCompress ok."<<std::endl; break;
7147  case Z_MEM_ERROR: std::cout<<"DeCompress not enough memory."<<std::endl; break;
7148  case Z_BUF_ERROR: std::cout<<"DeCompress not enough room in the output buffer."<<std::endl; break;
7149  case Z_DATA_ERROR: std::cout<<"DeCompress error data."<<std::endl; break;
7150  };
7151  } else {
7152  memcpy(ptr, p + 2 + 4,(unsigned)(sz - 2 - 4));
7153  }
7154 
7155  delete[] p;
7156 
7157  return ptr;
7158 }

7171 int sdlEventToCode(SDL_Event *event) {
7172  switch (event->type) {
7173  case SDL_KEYDOWN:
7174  case SDL_KEYUP:
7175  return event->key.keysym.scancode;
7176  case SDL_MOUSEBUTTONDOWN:
7177  case SDL_MOUSEBUTTONUP:
7178  switch (event->button.button) {
7179  case SDL_BUTTON_LEFT:
7180  return iMOUSE_LEFT_PRESS_CODE;
7181  case SDL_BUTTON_RIGHT:
7182  return iMOUSE_RIGHT_PRESS_CODE;
7183  }
7184  case SDL_MOUSEMOTION:
7185  if (event->motion.state & SDL_BUTTON_LMASK)
7186  return iMOUSE_LEFT_MOVE;
7187  else if (event->motion.state & SDL_BUTTON_RMASK)
7188  return iMOUSE_RIGHT_MOVE;
7189  else
7190  return iMOUSE_MOVE_CODE;
7191  }
7192  return -1;
7193 }
